<p>Kojima is personally hosting the event, but we don't know yet what will be discussed. The developer has numerous projects currently in the works, including the games <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/hideo-kojimas-od-release-date-gameplay-and-everything-we-know/1100-6533769/" data-ref-id="1100-6533769">OD</a> and <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/hideo-kojimas-physint-is-still-in-conceptual-stage/1100-6533807/" data-ref-id="1100-6533807">Physint</a>, along with a <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/death-stranding-movie-could-have-been-directed-by-kojima-himself/1100-6534300/" data-ref-id="1100-6534300">Death Stranding movie at A24</a> and a <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/adult-targeted-death-stranding-anime-movie-announced-joining-live-action-film/1100-6532527/" data-ref-id="1100-6532527">Death Stranding anime.</a></p><p>The newest version of Kojima Productions opened in December 2015, so it's coming up on its 10th anniversary. A previous iteration of Kojima Productions was <a href="https://deathstranding.fandom.com/wiki/Kojima_Productions" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">founded in 2005 and existed inside Konami </a>before Kojima <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/hideo-kojima-has-left-konami-and-kojima-production/1100-6431536/" data-ref-id="1100-6431536">left the company in 2015.</a></p><p>The new version of Kojima Productions has released two games so far, including Death Stranding (2019) and Death Stranding 2: On the Beach (2025). Kojima has said he has <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/kojima-has-already-written-death-stranding-3s-concept/1100-6534248/" data-ref-id="1100-6534248">ideas for Death Stranding 3, but he doesn't plan to make the game himself.</a></p><p>Kojima recently celebrated his 62nd birthday, and while others around that age may contemplate retirement, <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/kojima-turns-62-vows-to-keep-creating-for-remainder-of-his-life/1100-6534234/" data-ref-id="1100-6534234">Kojima said he plans to keep creating until he dies.</a></p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
